  <zone type="main">
    <line>The fiddle, the cry, the bowling marks</line>
    <line>Is to me a sufficiently hateful noise,</line>
    <line>They rage as by an evil spirit urged,</line>
    <line>And call it joy, call it Song.</line>
    <line>Peasants round the linden tree</line>
    <line>Dance &amp; Song</line>
    <line>The shepherd arrays himself for the Dance</line>
    <line>With coloured jerkin, band &amp; chaplet,</line>
    <line>Adorned was it to attract</line>
    <line>Already round the linden tree was it full,</line>
    <line>And all danced already like mad</line>
    <line>HUZZA, HUZZA</line>
    <line>HUZZA hello he</line>
    <line>So go the fiddle bows</line>
    <line>He presses hastily himself up</line>
    <line>Then pushes he to a maiden to,</line>
    <line>With his alder bow.</line>
    <line>The fresh girl turn herself round</line>
  </zone>
